{{Infobox book | name = CRC Concise Encyclopedia of Mathematics | image = CRC Concise Encyclopedia of Mathematics.jpg | caption = Cover of the second edition | author = [[Eric W. Weisstein]] | country = United States | language = English | subject = [[Mathematics]] | publisher = [[CRC Press]] | release_date = December 12, 2002 | media_type = Print ([[Hardcover]] and [[Paperback]]) and [[Compact disc|audio-CD]] | pages = 3252 | isbn = 1584883472 | dewey= | congress= | oclc= }}
'''''CRC Concise Encyclopedia of Mathematics''''' is a bestselling book by American author [[Eric W. Weisstein]].
==Summary==
The book is presented in a dictionary format. The book is divided into [[headword]]s. The book also provides relevant diagrams and illustrations.
==Lawsuits==
The book, quite notably became the subject of a lawsuit between [[CRC Press]] and [[Eric W. Weisstein]].<ref>[http://www.ericweisstein.com/authors-rights/authors_note.html ericweisstein.com]</ref>{{explain|date=September 2016}}
==Reception==
The book has consistently received good reviews.<ref>[http://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2600113-crc-concise-encyclopedia-of-mathematics goodreads.com]</ref><ref>[https://www.jstor.org/discover/10.2307/20453513?uid=2129&uid=2&uid=70&uid=4&sid=47699109134207 jstor.org]</ref><ref>[http://www.emeraldinsight.com/journals.htm?articleid=1497141 emeraldinsight.com]</ref>
==Editions==
* 1st edition, [[CRC Press]], 1999, {{ISBN|978-1-58488-347-0}} * 2nd edition, [[CRC Press]], 2002, {{ISBN|1584883472}} * 3rd edition, [[CRC Press]], 2005, {{ISBN|9780849319464}}
