The [[Chinle Formation]] is an [[Late Triassic|Upper Triassic]] continental [[geologic formation]] in the western United States which has yielded fossils of many [[archosaur]]s: a group of vertebrates that includes [[crocodile]]s, [[pterosaur]]s, [[dinosaur]]s (including birds), and other extinct relatives.
==Crurotarsans==
