s]]''<ref name="irmis2005-78-Saurosuchus">"Vertebrate Fauna; 'Rauisuchidae'; <nowiki>'</nowiki>''Saurosuchus'' sp.,<nowiki>'</nowiki>" Irmis (2005) p. 78</ref> | Indeterminate<ref name="irmis2005-78-Saurosuchus" /> | * Arizona<ref name="irmis2005-78-Saurosuchus" /> | * Blue Mesa<ref name="irmis2005-78-Saurosuchus" /> | | |- | ''[[Vivaron]]''<ref name="Lessner2016">Emily J. Lessner; Michelle R. Stocker; Nathan D. Smith; Alan H. Turner; Randall B. Irmis; Sterling J. Nesbitt (2016). "A new rauisuchid (Archosauria, Pseudosuchia) from the Upper Triassic (Norian) of New Mexico increases the diversity and temporal range of the clade". PeerJ. 4: e2336. doi:10.7717/peerj.2336.</ref> | ''V. haydeni''<ref name="Lessner2016" /> | * New Mexico<ref name="Lessner2016" /> | * Petrified Forest<ref name="Lessner2016" /> | | |- |}
