===Dinosaurs===
====Saurischians====
=====Sauropodomorphs===== Prosauropod tracks are present in the Redonda, Sloan Canyon, and Sheep Pen Sandstone formations. Possibly the Rock Point Formation as well. Geographically, the tracks are present in New Mexico.<ref name="triassicdistribution">Weishampel, David B; et al. (2004). "Dinosaur distribution (Late Triassic, North America)." In: Weishampel, David B.; Dodson, Peter; and Osmólska, Halszka (eds.): The Dinosauria, 2nd, Berkeley: University of California Press. Pp. 518–521. {{ISBN|0-520-24209-2}}.</ref>
=====Theropods and near-relatives===== Indeterminate ceratosaurian remains have been recovered from the Bull Canyon Formation in New Mexico.<ref name="triassicdistribution" /> Theropod tracks have been found in [[Utah]] and [[New Mexico]] recovered from the Redonda, Sloan Canyon, and Sheep Pen Sandstone formations.<ref name="triassicdistribution" /> Indeterminate theropod remains are stratigraphically present in the Santa Rosa, Petrified Forest, Bluewater Creek, Rock Point, and Garita Creek formations. They are geographically present in New Mexico.<ref name="triassicdistribution" /> Indeterminate herrerasaurid remains stratigraphically present in the Bull Canyon Formation and geographically present in New Mexico.<ref name="triassicdistribution" /> {| class="wikitable" align="center" width="100%" |- ! colspan="7" align="center" |'''[[Theropod]]s and near-relatives of the Chinle Formation''' |- ! Genus ! Species ! State ! Member ! Abundance ! Notes ! Images |- | ''[[Camposaurus]]''<ref name="triassicdistribution" /> | ''C. arizonensis''<ref name="triassicdistribution" /> | * Arizona<ref name="triassicdistribution" /> | * Bluewater Creek Formation<ref name="triassicdistribution" /> | | A [[Coelophysinae|coelophysine]] [[coelophysid]] | rowspan="99" | [[Image:Camposaurus arizonensis.png|thumb|center|200px|''[[Camposaurus]]'']] [[Image:Chindesaurus.jpeg|thumb|center|200px|''[[Chindesaurus]]'']] [[Image:Coelophysis-bauri head.jpg|thumb|center|200px|''[[Coelophysis bauri]]'']] [[Image:Daemonosaurus chauliodus.jpg|thumb|center|200px|''[[Daemonosaurus]]'']] [[Image:Gojirasaurus BW.jpg|thumb|center|200px|''[[Gojirasaurus]]'']] [[Image:Tawa hallae dino 01.JPG|thumb|center|200px|''[[Tawa (dinosaur)|Tawa]]'']] |- | ''[[Chindesaurus]]''<ref name="triassicdistribution" /> | ''C. bryansmalli''<ref name="triassicdistribution" /> | * Arizona<ref name="triassicdistribution" /> * <small>New Mexico</small><ref name="triassicdistribution" /> | * <small>Bull Canyon Formation</small><ref name="triassicdistribution" /> * Petrified Forest<ref name="triassicdistribution" /> | | A [[herrerasaur]] |- | rowspan="4" | ''[[Coelophysis]]''<ref name="triassicdistribution" /> | ''C. bauri'' | * New Mexico<ref name=zeigleretal08>{{cite journal |last=Zeigler |first=K. E. |author2=Kelley, S.|author3= Geissman, J. W. |year=2008 |title=Revisions to stratigraphic nomenclature of the Upper Triassic Chinle Group in New Mexico: New insights from geologic mapping, sedimentology, and magnetostratigraphic/paleomagnetic data |journal=Rocky Mountain Geology |volume=43 |pages=121–141 |doi=10.2113/gsrocky.43.2.121 |issue=2}}</ref> | * Siltstone<ref name=zeigleretal08/> | |- |''C.'' sp.<ref name="irmis2005-7172-Coelophysis-sp">"Vertebrate Fauna; Pseudosuchia; ''Revueltosaurus callenderi''," Irmis (2005) p. 81</ref> | *Arizona<ref name="irmis2005-7172-Coelophysis-sp"/> | *Petrified Forest<ref name="irmis2005-7172-Coelophysis-sp"/> | | Originally assigned to ''C. bauri'', is likely a different [[taxon]].<ref name="irmis2005-7172-Coelophysis-sp"/> |- |style="background:#E6E6E6;" | ''C. longicollis''<ref name="triassicdistribution" /> |style="background:#E6E6E6;" | * New Mexico<ref name="triassicdistribution" /> |style="background:#E6E6E6;" | * Petrified Forest<ref name="triassicdistribution" /> |style="background:#E6E6E6;" | |style="background:#E6E6E6;" | Now considered a junior synonym of ''C. bauri''. |- |style="background:#E6E6E6;" | ''C. willistoni'' |style="background:#E6E6E6;" | * New Mexico<ref name="triassicdistribution" /> |style="background:#E6E6E6;" | * Petrified Forest<ref name="triassicdistribution" /> |style="background:#E6E6E6;" | |style="background:#E6E6E6;" | Now considered a junior synonym of ''C. bauri''. |- | ''[[Daemonosaurus]]'' | ''D. chauliodus'' | * New Mexico | * "Siltstone" | | A basal theropod |- | ''[[Gojirasaurus]]''<ref name="triassicdistribution" /> | ''G. quayi''<ref name="triassicdistribution" /> | * New Mexico<ref name="triassicdistribution" /> | * Cooper Canyon<ref name="triassicdistribution" /> | | A [[coelophysoid]] |- | ''[[Tawa (dinosaur)|Tawa]]'' | ''T. hallae'' | * New Mexico | | | A basal theropod |- |}
